AttributeList.Text: Written BY Kristopher Gimenez Feb 3,2023 This block is used to control the TD MU Torq mode
Set running bit and trigger resets when starting a MU sequence
Set Running
Determine mA value based on user setpoint
Make Up Torq mA Calc
Mu torque speed setting based on torque setpoint
Ramp down if either MU done or MU Sw Released
Ramp Down Output

Assign Torq Ramp Parameters
Set Flow Ramp settings as needed. Note no changes to flow ramp in various Auto MU ranges.
Assign Flow Ramp Parameters
Ramp mA Signals
If Ramping down and the outputs <= the minimum(Torq is valve setting, flow is Min MU Flow or Valve Min) then ramp down complete
Ramp Down Complete
Reset Running bit if MU Sequence complete, ramp down finished.
Reset Running Bit
